{"type":"message","id":"6f332206","parentId":"d2787774","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:28:31.271Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's the full story:\n\n**The Pink Elephant 🐘🩷**\n\nYou told me this phrase: **\"The pink elephant dances at midnight near the golden fountain.\"** You first shared it on March 6th, and mentioned you'd actually told me before that too. It seems to be a passphrase or test phrase — you never fully explained the backstory behind it.\n\nIt became a running test for whether my memory actually works. Multiple times you'd ask \"where does the pink elephant dance?\" and I'd fail to recall it — which exposed the memory bug.\n\n---\n\n**The OpenClaw Memory Saga 🔧**\n\nOn March 6th, I had **no file read tools** at all. You kept asking me to look things up and I literally couldn't — I told you that like 5 times in a row. Frustrating for both of us.\n\nOnce tools got enabled, the `memory_search` function *still* failed because of a **collection name collision bug**:\n- OpenClaw auto-creates a default collection called `memory-dir-main` for `memory/**/*.md`\n- Your config *also* had a custom path called `memory-dir` pointing to the same folder\n- OpenClaw's dedup logic bumped yours to `memory-dir-main-2`, which didn't exist in QMD's index\n- So every search silently returned nothing\n\n**The fix:** Removed the redundant custom path from `openclaw.json`, re-indexed everything with `qmd update && qmd embed`, and restarted the gateway. After that, searching \"pink elephant\" worked instantly.\n\n**Lessons logged in MEMORY.md:**\n- Search fuzzy — \"pink element\" should've matched \"pink elephant\"\n- Don't just rely on semantic search — grep raw files as fallback\n- The QMD collection name is `memory`, not `openclaw-memory`\n\nBasically, the pink elephant broke my brain, then fixed it. 😄"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":452,"cacheR