{"type":"message","id":"a4d8981c","parentId":"d49f0a82","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:30:40.642Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01PF9acjv5dHsS4AKNf5w28q","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-06 23:58:59 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 78d9d68c-26e2-4418-bf3d-d4d0a754009b\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nassistant: Hey — I'm online. Friday evening, fresh session. What are we working on?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 18:51 EST] tell me about elephant we said in the past\nassistant: I don't have any memory of a past conversation about elephants — each session starts fresh, and I don't have any previous context loaded that mentions them.\n\nIf you jot down what you were referring to, I'm happy to pick up from there. Or if it was something you want me to remember going forward, just tell me and I'll write it down.\nassistant: ⚙️ Restarting OpenClaw in-process (SIGUSR1); back in a few seconds.\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 18:53 EST] What do you remember?\nassistant: Honestly? Right now, not much — this session started clean. Here's what I actually have on file:\n\n- **Location:** Columbia, SC · **Timezone:** Eastern\n- **Workspace:** fresh, no significant history logged yet\n- The workspace files (SOUL, AGENTS, TOOLS, USER) are all mostly default/unfilled — your name, preferences, projects, etc. haven't been filled in yet.\n\nIf we've talked before, either the memory files weren't written or this is genuinely a fresh setup. Want to fix that? Tell me a bit about yourself and what you're working on — I'll write it down so future-me actually knows who you are.\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 18:53 EST] tell me about our past conversation\nassistant: There's only one session on record — and it's this one, which started today. There's no prior conversation history I can pull from.\n\nThis could mean a few things:\n- OpenClaw was recently installed or reset\n- Past sessions weren't persisted\n- We haven't actually talked before under this setup\n\nEither way, I'm starting from scratch. If you want continuity going forward, tell me things worth remembering and I'll write them down. What's on your mind?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 18:54 EST] Are we using QMD memory system?\nassistant: Not that I'm aware of — I don't have any configuration or files referencing a \"QMD memory system\" in this workspace. My memory setup is just the standard flat-file approach: `MEMORY.md` for long-term stuff and `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` daily logs.\n\nIs QMD something you set up previously or wanted to implement? If you can point me to it or describe it, I can take a look and get it wired up.\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 18:55 EST] I implemented QMD (https://github.com/tobi/qmd) and help be debug and test it if it is working or not\nassistant: Got it! Let me poke around the workspace and see what's actually there.\nassistant: Hmm, I don't have a shell/exec tool in this environment — I can't run commands directly. To check if QMD is wired up, could you run these and paste the output?\n\n```bash\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ 2>/dev/null\nwhich qmd 2>/dev/null || echo \"qmd not found in PATH\"\n```\n\nThat'll tell me if QMD dropped any files, if the memory directory exists, and whether the `qmd` binary is accessible. From there I can help you