{"type":"message","id":"3e094587","parentId":"a4d8981c","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:30:40.690Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_019GwCAfYCETmcjDqdYr4Nec","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-07 00:42:27 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: f75e9a38-aece-418e-97f5-437c4c09876a\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:32 EST] we discuss before\nassistant: Nothing's coming up in my memory about this — fresh session, and no prior notes on pink elephants dancing. If we talked about it before, it didn't make it into my memory files. What were we discussing? I'm happy to pick back up!\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:32 EST] cmd update\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:32 EST] cmd update\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:33 EST] qmd update\nassistant: Done! Memory index updated — 2 new files, 1 updated across both workspace and memory collections. You can run `qmd embed` if you want the vector embeddings refreshed too. Want me to do that?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:33 EST] Where do pink elephant dance?\nassistant: Still the same answer — in your dreams, where the music never stops. 🐘✨\n\nWas there something specific we discussed about this before that you're trying to recall?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:34 EST] tell me about \"pink elephant\" we discussed\nassistant: Nothing in my memory about \"pink elephant\" — whatever we talked about, it wasn't written down, so it didn't survive the session reset. \n\nIf you fill me in on what we covered, I'm happy to pick up where we left off — and this time I'll make sure to log it. 📝\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:36 EST] Are you using QMD to search memory we archived? How did you search memory\nassistant: Good question. I use a built-in `memory_search` tool that's supposed to query your memory files via qmd. But as you saw — it kept timing out (`qmd query ... timed out after 4000ms`), so the searches came back empty. That's why I couldn't pull up any prior \"pink elephant\" discussion.\n\nThe index itself updated fine when you ran `qmd update`, but the search/query side seems to be having issues. Want me to try querying qmd directly from the shell to see if that works better?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:38 EST] yes do it\nassistant: The direct shell query hangs too — same timeout issue. The warning says 3 documents need embeddings, which might be related. Let me run `qmd embed` first and then try the search again:\nassistant: It's downloading a reranking model (~639MB) — first-time setup for the query engine. Let me wait for it to finish…\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773081040689}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0236a96","parentId":"3e094587","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:30:40.696Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01Tep8SFYSWzqB7fBnfeUbxJ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-07 00:55:17 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: af84a6be-804d-42bf-ba92-32f25a2a7abe\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nuser: A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nassistant: Hey Nay! Back online and ready to roll. What are we getting into today?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:43 EST] Are you using QMD to search memory we archived? How did you search memory\nassistant: [[reply_to_current]] Two things happened when I started up:\n\n1. **`memory_search` tool** — tried to use QMD under the hood, but it errored out with `Collection not found: memory-main`, so it got zero results from that path.\n\n2. **Direct file read via `exec`** — I listed the `memory/` folder and catted today's date file, which is how I actually got context (saw the pink elephant note from 2026-03-06).\n\nSo effectively: QMD search failed silently, and I fell back to raw file reading. The memory search infrastructure seems like it's either not initialized or the collection hasn't been built yet. Want me to dig into why QMD isn't finding the collection?\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773081040695}}
{"type":"message","id":"e4fdd53f","parentId":"f0236a96","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:30:40.706Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01CpKyYnnPFKT1tM2qafPicZ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-07 01:00:36 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 3666bd80-f5c0-4294-ab03-2db8e63caf53\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nassistant: Hey Nay — back online. What are we working on today?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:55 EST] Are you using QMD to search memory we archived? How did you search memory\nassistant: The `memory_search` tool tried to use QMD but it failed — the error was `Collection not found: memory-dir-main`, so it fell back to FTS-only mode and came back empty. Effectively, no memory was retrieved this session.\n\nIf you've archived memory files, they may not be indexed yet in QMD, or the collection hasn't been set up. Want me to dig into what's going on with the memory setup?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:57 EST] give me structure of 'main.sqlite' file\nassistant: Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Core Tables:**\n- **`meta`** — key/value store for DB metadata (version, config, etc.)\n- **`files`** — tracks indexed files: path, source, hash, mtime, size\n- **`chunks`** — the meat: text chunks with embeddings, line ranges, model used, source path\n- **`embedding_cache`** — caches embeddings by provider/model/hash so they don't get re-generated\n\n**FTS (Full-Text Search) Virtual Tables:**\n- **`chunks_fts`** — FTS5 index over `chunks.text` for keyword search\n- Plus the standard FTS5 backing tables (`_data`, `_idx`, `_content`, `_docsize`, `_config`)\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_chunks_path` and `idx_chunks_source` on the chunks table\n- `idx_embedding_cache_updated_at` for cache expiry/cleanup\n\nSo it supports both **semantic search** (via stored embeddings in `chunks`) and **FTS keyword search** (via `chunks_fts`). The QMD error earlier suggests the collection name `memory-dir-main` wasn't matching — want me to check what's actually in the `meta` table or what files are indexed?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:57 EST] yes\nassistant: The DB is **empty** — no meta entries, no files indexed, no chunks. That's why QMD failed; the collection exists as a file but has never been populated.\n\nThe memory search tool tried to query a collection called `memory-dir-main` and found nothing because nothing's been indexed yet. Your `.md` memory files exist in the workspace but haven't been fed into this SQLite DB.\n\nWant me to check if there's an indexing command or config that should be running to populate it?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:57 EST] cmd update\nassistant: So the actual index is at a **different path** than I checked:\n`~/.openclaw/agents/main/qmd/xdg-cache/qmd/index.sqlite`\n\nAnd it's actually healthy — **27 files, 27 chunks indexed, vector ready**. The `main.sqlite` I looked at earlier was a red herring (empty, different location).\n\nThe earlier `memory_search` failure with `Collection not found: memory-dir-main` is odd given status shows it's fine. To force a reindex:\n\n```\nopenclaw memory index --force\n```\n\nWant me to run that, or first try a test search to see if it works now?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:58 EST] openclaw memory index --force\nassistant: Done. Index updated successfully. There's also a doctor warning about Telegram — group messages are being silently dropped because `groupAllowFrom` is empty and `groupPolicy` is set to `allowlist`. Worth fixing if you want Telegram group access working.\n\nWant me to test a memory search now to confirm it's pulling correctly?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:58 EST] yes, test\nassistant: Still failing — same error: `Collection not found: memory-dir-main`. The index is populated but the tool is looking for a collection named `memory-dir-main` that doesn't exist in QMD. Let me check what collections actually exist:\nassistant: Found it. The collections are named **`memory-main`** and **`workspace-main`** — but the `memory_search` tool is calling with `memory-dir-main`. That's a mismatch in the collection name the tool is passing to QMD. This looks like a bug or a config/version mismatch in OpenClaw. The data is there, the index is fine — the tool just has the wrong collection name hardcoded.\n\nWorth reporting or checking if there's a config option to override it. Want me to dig into the OpenClaw config to see if it's adjustable?\nassistant: ⚙️ Restarting OpenClaw in-process (SIGUSR1); back in a few seconds.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773081040704}}
