{"type":"message","id":"1b9d252e","parentId":"f1f4c755","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:30:44.086Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01BfgFvNJZ6HB12Ajz3rBVFZ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-07 00:26:01 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 8cdec542-c899-4726-ac34-46e29bb50666\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nuser: A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nassistant: Hey Nay! Back online and ready to roll. What are we working on today?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:23 EST] update QMD memory\nassistant: QMD memory is now updated. Here's what happened:\n\n- **workspace** collection: 4 new files indexed (the new daily memory files from today's sessions), 2 updated\n- **memory** collection: 4 new files indexed (the session summaries that were missing), 1 updated\n- All 19 documents now have fresh vector embeddings\n\nEverything from today's sessions — including your name, the QMD setup, the weather check, the pink elephant test — is now searchable. What's next?\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773081044085}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3c39980","parentId":"1b9d252e","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:30:44.093Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01TWJeAa1hXi5mujhzvPiUqd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-08 17:37:30 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: bb32552b-0c87-4e9e-9e96-f33adedf74d3\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nuser: A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Sunday, March 8th, 2026 — 1:03 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-08 17:03 UTC\nassistant: Hey Nay! 🐙 Back online and ready to go. What are we getting into today?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-08 13:03 EDT] Show me usage and balance of Claude AI\nassistant: Here's what I found:\n\n**🔑 API Key Status:** Configured and working (`sk-ant-oat01-xwTBrp…`)\n\n**📊 Current Session Token Usage (OpenClaw sessions):**\n\n| Session | Model | Input | Output | Cache Read | Total |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| webchat (main) | claude-sonnet-4-6 | 5 | 301 | 12,008 | 12,299 |\n| telegram (direct) | claude-sonnet-4-6 | 3 | 186 | — | — |\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ Balance & Aggregate Usage:** Anthropic doesn't expose billing/credit balance or historical usage via the public REST API — those are only available through the web console.\n\nTo check your balance and full usage history, go to:\n👉 **[console.anthropic.com/settings/billing](https://console.anthropic.com/settings/billing)**\n👉 **[console.anthropic.com/settings/usage](https://console.anthropic.com/settings/usage)**\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-08 13:27 EDT] Can you. browser those link\nassistant: No luck on two fronts:\n\n1. **Browser not available** — OpenClaw's browser tool requires Chrome/Brave/Edge/Chromium, but none are detected on this machine.\n2. **Console API** — The Anthropic console (billing/usage) uses browser-based auth (session cookies), so curl won't work without a logged-in session.\n\nI can pop the links open in your default macOS browser if you'd like:\nassistant: Done — opened both links in your default browser:\n- **Billing & balance** → `console.anthropic.com/settings/billing`\n- **Usage history** → `console.anthropic.com/settings/usage`\n\nYou may need to log in if you're not already. Once you're in, you'll see your credit balance and token usage breakdown there.\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-08 13:34 EDT] I am using claude oauth. not api\nassistant: Got it — that changes things. With Claude OAuth (Claude.ai subscription), there's no credit balance to check — it's a subscription plan with usage limits, not pay-per-token billing.\nassistant: Claude.ai is behind Cloudflare — won't work without a real browser session with cookies. Here's the deal:\n\n**With Claude OAuth (Pro/Team subscription):**\n- No credit balance — it's a flat subscription\n- Usage limits are message-rate based (not dollar-based)\n- Only Anthropic's console/claude.ai shows it\n\nLet me open the right page for you:\nassistant: Opened `claude.ai/settings/billing` — that's where you'll see your plan, renewal date, and any usage limits. There's no token/dollar counter with OAuth; it's just your subscription tier (Free / Pro / Team / Enterprise).\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-08 13:36 EDT] Yes, I want to know how much percentage used and left\nassistant: Got it from the API rate limit headers! Here's your Claude usage:\n\n**⏱ 5-Hour Window**\n- Used: **11%** · Left: **89%**\n- Resets at **6:00 PM today** (in ~4h 22m)\n\n**📅 7-Day Window**\n- Used: **3%** · Left: **97%**\n- Resets **Saturday Mar 14** (~6 days from now)\n\nYou've got plenty of headroom on both. 🟢\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773081044090}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9d38df9","parentId":"f3c39980","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:31:13.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Alright, here's the detailed timeline from memory only:\n\n---\n\n### 📅 March 6 (Friday) — The Frustrating Day\n\n**Round 1 — No tools at all.**\nYou kept asking me \"tell me about the elephant we discussed\" and I had zero file-reading capability. No `exec`, no `read`, no `memory_search`. I told you this like 5+ times. You asked me to run `memory_search` and I literally couldn't — the tool wasn't available. You asked about QMD and I didn't even know what it was.\n\n**Round 2 — Tools enabled, but QMD broken.**\nAfter a restart, I got shell access. You told me you implemented QMD (github.com/tobi/qmd) and wanted help testing it. We discovered:\n- The agent-specific QMD SQLite DB (`main.sqlite`) was **completely empty** — zero files, zero chunks\n- The actual index lived at a different path (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/qmd/xdg-cache/qmd/index.sqlite`) and was healthy (27 files indexed)\n- But `memory_search` kept failing with **\"Collection not found: memory-dir-main\"** — the tool was requesting a collection name that didn't exist in QMD\n\n**Round 3 — You told me the phrase.**\nAfter all that frustration, you just told me directly: **\"The pink elephant dances at midnight near the golden fountain.\"** I saved it to `memory/2026-03-06.md`. You said you'd told me before but I couldn't find it.\n\n**Round 4 — Found the root cause.**\nThe bug: OpenClaw auto-creates default collections (`memory-root-main`, `memory-alt-main`, `memory-dir-main`). Your `openclaw.json` also had a custom path called `memory-dir` pointing to the same `memory/` folder. OpenClaw's `ensureUniqueName()` bumped your custom one to `memory-dir-main-2`, which didn't exist in QMD's index. **Name collision = silent failure.**\n\n**The fix:** Removed the redundant custom `memory-dir` path from config, re-indexed with `qmd update && qmd embed`, restarted the gateway. After that, searching \"pink elephant\" worked instantly.\n\n**Also:** First-time `qmd embed` had to download a ~639MB reranking model, which took a while.\n\n---\n\n### 📅 March 7 (Saturday)\n\nWe discussed elephants more broadly — their emotional complexity, ecosystem engineering, intelligence. Then you tested me again on \"where do pink elephants dance?\" This time `memory_search` actually worked and returned the phrase correctly.\n\nAlso updated QMD memory index — 4 new files indexed across workspace and memory collections, all embedded.\n\n---\n\n### 📅 March 8 (Sunday)\n\nShifted topics. You asked about Claude AI usage/balance. We figured out you're on **Claude OAuth (Pro subscription)**, not API billing. I checked rate-limit headers and found: **11% of 5-hour window used, 3% of 7-day window used.** Also checked weather for Columbia, SC.\n\n---\n\n### 📅 March 9 (Monday — today, earlier via webchat)\n\nYou asked me to explain pink elephant and how I got the answer step by step. I walked through it — memory_search, QMD query, grep fallback. Then you asked about real pink elephant locations (Myanmar, Thailand, Africa) and I answered from training knowledge. You pushed me to redo it using memory search, and the memory only contained what I'd told you previously.\n\n---\n\n### 🧠 Lessons Logged in MEMORY.md\n\n1. **Search fuzzy** — \"pink element\" ≠ \"pink elephant\" but should've matched\n2. **Read raw daily files** before saying \"I don't know\" — the answer was sitting there\n3. **Don't rely only on QMD/memory_search** — grep as fallback\n4. **QMD collection is `memory`, NOT `openclaw-memory`** — was silently failing"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":965,"cacheRead":28523,"cacheWrite":1894,"totalTokens":31383,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.024125,"cacheRead":0.0142615,"cacheWrite":0.0118375,"total":0.050229}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773081044092}}
